WEBVTT

1
00:00:50.300 --> 00:00:55.137
CROWD [CHANTING]:
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

2
00:01:00.769 --> 00:01:03.103
[BILL CONTI'S "GONNA FLY NOW"
PLAYING]

3
00:01:22.791 --> 00:01:24.208
[CROWD CHEERING]

4
00:01:38.098 --> 00:01:40.140
[CROWD BOOING]

5
00:01:40.308 --> 00:01:42.643
[♪♪♪]

6
00:01:44.312 --> 00:01:45.813
[BELL RINGS]

7
00:01:47.857 --> 00:01:51.276
COMMENTATOR 1:
<i>Yet another quick knockout for
Mason Dixon, almost perfunctory.</i>

8
00:01:51.486 --> 00:01:53.529
<i>The fans let him know
how they feel about it.</i>

9
00:01:53.696 --> 00:01:56.698
COMMENTATOR 2:
<i>Hide the women and children.
This could get ugly.</i>

10
00:01:56.866 --> 00:02:00.994
COMMENTATOR 1:
<i>This crowd does nothing to hide
its anger over this latest debacle.</i>

11
00:02:01.371 --> 00:02:04.206
<i>The fans are mad as hell.
They don't want to take it anymore.</i>

12
00:02:04.415 --> 00:02:07.334
<i>They seem to be blaming Dixon,
a good fighter, for the decline,</i>

13
00:02:07.502 --> 00:02:11.755
<i>not only of the heavyweight-division
guys, but of the entire sport.</i>

14
00:02:11.923 --> 00:02:13.382
COMMENTATOR 3:
<i>They're actually pelting</i>

15
00:02:13.550 --> 00:02:17.094
<i>the undefeated heavyweight
champion of the world with ice.</i>

16
00:02:17.262 --> 00:02:20.973
COMMENTATOR 1:
<i>Maybe this angry, visceral reaction
will pressure Dixon to fight someone</i>

17
00:02:21.141 --> 00:02:24.059
<i>who can fight back for a change.
If there's somebody out there.</i>

18
00:02:24.227 --> 00:02:29.481
COMMENTATOR 2:
<i>All of boxing is hoping for a warrior
who thrills us with his passion.</i>

19
00:02:31.609 --> 00:02:34.778
[FRANK STALLONE
AND VALENTINE'S
"TAKE YOU BACK" PLAYING]

20
00:03:21.117 --> 00:03:23.118
[ALARM BUZZING]

21
00:03:24.454 --> 00:03:25.537
[BUZZING STOPS]

22
00:03:25.705 --> 00:03:27.706
[♪♪♪]

23
00:04:08.248 --> 00:04:10.332
[GRUNTING]

24
00:04:57.547 --> 00:04:59.673
Time goes by too fast.

25
00:04:59.841 --> 00:05:03.093
Yeah? Not fast enough.

26
00:05:03.261 --> 00:05:05.512
Your kid should've been here.
That's all right, Paulie.

27
00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:06.763
No, it ain't all right.

28
00:05:06.931 --> 00:05:09.057
Ah, you know, the kid
gets a little busy sometimes.

29
00:05:09.267 --> 00:05:10.934
He don't get that busy.

30
00:05:11.227 --> 00:05:15.397
Well, let's not talk about it here,
okay? You're coming tonight, right?

31
00:05:15.565 --> 00:05:19.276
I'm working. I took the tour
the last three years.

32
00:05:19.444 --> 00:05:21.570
I know,
but it's the anniversary.

33
00:05:21.738 --> 00:05:23.363
Fine.
You got my word.

34
00:05:23.531 --> 00:05:27.993
I appreciate it, thank you.
I owe you, Paulie.

35
00:05:59.567 --> 00:06:02.736
Yo, Robert. What's going on?
Where have you been? You're late.

36
00:06:04.530 --> 00:06:05.906
I, uh--
No. I don't wanna hear this.

37
00:06:06.074 --> 00:06:10.327
Look, your job performance
is nowhere near good enough
to be pulling this.

38
00:06:10.495 --> 00:06:13.497
I don't give a damn who your
father is. You understand me?
All right.

39
00:06:13.664 --> 00:06:15.957
All right. Now get out of here.
Okay.

40
00:06:16.125 --> 00:06:17.834
Thank you, sir.

41
00:06:20.171 --> 00:06:21.213
Yo, Robert.

42
00:06:21.381 --> 00:06:22.506
Yo.

43
00:06:22.673 --> 00:06:24.466
Hey, Rocky.
Hey.

44
00:06:24.801 --> 00:06:25.967
Hey, how you doing?
Hey.

45
00:06:26.135 --> 00:06:27.636
MAN:
What's up, champ?

46
00:06:27.804 --> 00:06:29.721
You caught me off guard.
I know I caught you off guard.

47
00:06:29.889 --> 00:06:31.640
I wanted to catch you
before you got too busy.

48
00:06:31.808 --> 00:06:33.475
Yeah, it gets busy up there.

49
00:06:33.643 --> 00:06:36.228
So how you doing? Yeah?
Real good. Yeah.

50
00:06:36.646 --> 00:06:39.648
Yo, Rock!
Yeah, how you doing?

51
00:06:39.816 --> 00:06:41.441
Yeah, real good.

52
00:06:41.609 --> 00:06:44.194
Hey, listen, you wanna go out
and get some coffee?

53
00:06:44.362 --> 00:06:46.071
I'm kind of behind.
Maybe later?

54
00:06:46.572 --> 00:06:49.658
Yeah. That'd be great. You ought
to come by the restaurant tonight.

55
00:06:49.826 --> 00:06:52.244
I can have something
made special for you.

56
00:06:52.412 --> 00:06:56.331
Tonight I can't. I got plans.
A few of the guys get together.

57
00:06:56.874 --> 00:06:59.543
Did I do something wrong?
What do you mean?

58
00:06:59.710 --> 00:07:02.421
Well, I don't know exactly
what I mean,

59
00:07:02.588 --> 00:07:06.508
but I just think, like, when I come
here, you don't feel so comfortable.

60
00:07:06.717 --> 00:07:09.010
And I certainly
don't wanna do that.

61
00:07:10.346 --> 00:07:13.390
Well, you throw a big shadow.
A big shadow?

62
00:07:13.558 --> 00:07:16.184
TOMILSON:
You're not gonna get anything
done down here, Robert.

63
00:07:16.352 --> 00:07:18.353
Well, if you're not gonna
introduce me, then I will.

64
00:07:18.521 --> 00:07:20.063
Hi, I'm William Tomilson.
How you doing?

65
00:07:20.231 --> 00:07:22.107
Your son has the misfortune
of working for me.

66
00:07:22.650 --> 00:07:24.359
It's a good job.
Yeah.

67
00:07:24.527 --> 00:07:27.362
You know, I gotta tell you,
I've told Robert about 20 times
that I wanted to meet you.

68
00:07:27.530 --> 00:07:29.698
I guess you're pretty busy,
which isn't a bad thing.

69
00:07:29.866 --> 00:07:32.242
I get a little tied up.
Hey, look, grab a shot, will you?

70
00:07:32.869 --> 00:07:36.079
I may not get this chance again.
Us old warhorses have got to
stick together, don't we?

71
00:07:36.247 --> 00:07:38.582
The old horses, yeah.
I'll tell you.

72
00:07:38.791 --> 00:07:40.500
Whoa. Good thing
it's not your left.

73
00:07:40.668 --> 00:07:42.544
This makes you very
popular with people.

74
00:07:42.920 --> 00:07:45.881
One, two, three.
Finally, we get to meet.

75
00:07:46.048 --> 00:07:48.758
Look, I gotta get going. It was
nice to meet you face to face.

76
00:07:48.926 --> 00:07:52.304
You take care of yourself.
Robert, I'll see you later.

77
00:07:54.724 --> 00:07:58.268
I gotta get going. I'll change
my plans for tonight.

78
00:07:58.436 --> 00:08:00.312
That'd be great.
I'm looking forward to it.

79
00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:01.897
How you doing?
Okay.

80
00:08:02.064 --> 00:08:03.899
Okay.
All right.

81
00:08:04.066 --> 00:08:07.444
And do not let those numbers
drive you crazy.

82
00:08:07.612 --> 00:08:11.698
Too late.
Use an eraser, get rid of all of them.

83
00:08:13.784 --> 00:08:15.035
MAN 1: Yo, Rock.
ROCKY: Hey, guys.

84
00:08:15.411 --> 00:08:17.454
MAN 2: Hey, Rock.
ROCKY: Hey, how you doing?

85
00:08:17.663 --> 00:08:19.915
[♪♪♪]

86
00:08:30.760 --> 00:08:32.427
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

87
00:08:32.929 --> 00:08:33.929
There you go.

88
00:08:39.602 --> 00:08:43.063
It'll be about 1 0 tenths.
You guys take care, okay?
You got it.

89
00:08:46.359 --> 00:08:48.401
Tell you what,
I'll try a few of these later on.

90
00:08:49.237 --> 00:08:51.780
It's good for baking.
How much--?

91
00:08:51.948 --> 00:08:53.907
Yo, Paul, what's the cost?
MAN: 58.40, sir.

92
00:08:54.075 --> 00:08:56.451
All right, take it out of that.
I trust you.

93
00:08:58.788 --> 00:09:00.455
MAN: How you doing?
You're too generous.

94
00:09:00.623 --> 00:09:02.374
Not a problem.

95
00:09:18.474 --> 00:09:20.934
How you guys doing?

96
00:09:27.275 --> 00:09:29.359
How we doing, Isabel?

97
00:09:29.527 --> 00:09:31.945
Okay, except for the freebie
reading the Bible over there.

98
00:09:32.113 --> 00:09:33.780
Ah, he's okay.
You know, just because

99
00:09:33.948 --> 00:09:37.617
you fought him don't mean
you gotta feed him forever.
He doesn't even look like a fighter.

100
00:09:37.785 --> 00:09:39.452
Spider Rico could hit.

101
00:09:39.620 --> 00:09:42.163
Listen, how's your stomach?
It's okay.

102
00:09:42.373 --> 00:09:44.666
If you keep rubbing that
olive oil on your stomach,

103
00:09:44.834 --> 00:09:46.835
your kid's gonna be
born very strong.

104
00:09:47.003 --> 00:09:49.879
Okay, Rocky. Whatever you say.
No, really.

105
00:09:52.758 --> 00:09:55.343
Yo, how you doing, Spider?
God bless you, Rocky.

106
00:09:55.553 --> 00:09:56.803
Thanks.

107
00:09:57.013 --> 00:09:59.472
[MUSIC PLAYING OVER RADIO]

108
00:10:02.101 --> 00:10:04.102
How you guys doing?

109
00:10:05.938 --> 00:10:09.774
Jose, can you make something
special for my kid who's coming
tonight?

110
00:10:09.984 --> 00:10:11.234
JOSE:
No problemo.

111
00:10:11.402 --> 00:10:14.529
Good. I appreciate it.

112
00:10:16.240 --> 00:10:19.200
ROCKY:
<i>Back and forth, back and forth,
give and take.</i>

113
00:10:19.368 --> 00:10:22.621
And then I went in there
like an animal and I threw
him into the corner

114
00:10:22.788 --> 00:10:26.499
and I unloaded everything I had.
Hook, hook, hook, left, left, left.

115
00:10:26.667 --> 00:10:29.294
But Creed, he kept
busting me back pretty good,

116
00:10:29.462 --> 00:10:31.379
and the agony
began to pile up.

117
00:10:31.547 --> 00:10:34.883
Then I heard the best sound
that I ever heard in my life...

118
00:10:35.051 --> 00:10:36.676
The bell.
That's right, the bell.

119
00:10:36.844 --> 00:10:40.013
And I ain't never been so tired,
and I'm sitting in my corner.

120
00:10:40.181 --> 00:10:42.807
And I'm trying to figure out
how to survive the last round,

121
00:10:42.975 --> 00:10:44.809
when Mickey leans
into my ear and says:

122
00:10:44.977 --> 00:10:48.063
"Come on, get out there
and fight this guy hard, you bum.

123
00:10:48.230 --> 00:10:53.068
You gotta be first. You gotta be first."
I said, "Yo, Mick, if I could...

124
00:10:53.235 --> 00:10:56.029
ALL: "I would."
I would."

125
00:10:56.197 --> 00:10:57.280
The end.

126
00:10:57.448 --> 00:10:59.074
ALL: <i>Salud.
Salud.</i>

127
00:10:59.241 --> 00:11:02.243
[RICH BOY'S "BOY LOOKA HERE"
PLAYING]

128
00:11:19.428 --> 00:11:20.762
[CROWD CHEERING]

129
00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:22.222
[PUNCHES LANDING]

130
00:11:22.640 --> 00:11:24.182
[♪♪♪]

131
00:11:24.350 --> 00:11:27.435
COMMENTATOR 1:
<i>Yet another quick knockout for
Mason Dixon, almost perfunctory.</i>

132
00:11:27.603 --> 00:11:30.271
<i>The fans let him know
how they feel about it.</i>

133
00:11:30.439 --> 00:11:32.023
COMMENTATOR 2:
<i>They're actually pelting</i>

134
00:11:32.191 --> 00:11:36.569
<i>the undefeated heavyweight
champion of the world with ice.</i>

135
00:11:36.737 --> 00:11:38.405
[PHONE RINGING]

136
00:11:41.826 --> 00:11:45.120
Hello, Adrian's. Yeah?

137
00:11:45.663 --> 00:11:49.999
Tell him you can't make it?
Yeah, I'll give him the message.

138
00:11:51.419 --> 00:11:55.547
I just kept hearing Mickey's voice
in my head over and over again.

139
00:11:55.756 --> 00:11:57.632
I just dug down,
and before you know it,

140
00:11:57.800 --> 00:12:01.010
it was toe to toe and it was--
Excuse me.

141
00:12:01.178 --> 00:12:05.432
Your son said he can't make it.
He said he'll take a rain check.
Okay?

142
00:12:05.599 --> 00:12:08.268
[♪♪♪]

143
00:12:18.821 --> 00:12:20.029
ROCKY:
<i>Look at these birds.</i>

144
00:12:20.197 --> 00:12:22.991
<i>Don't these birds look like candy?
flying candy?</i>

145
00:12:23.159 --> 00:12:25.076
<i>Hey, birdie,
you wanna fly me home?</i>

146
00:12:25.244 --> 00:12:27.787
You need somebody
to walk you home?

147
00:12:28.706 --> 00:12:29.706
<i>No?</i>

148
00:12:29.874 --> 00:12:34.794
It's a cold night. We need
a few laughs in our life.
What do you think? Maybe?

149
00:12:35.463 --> 00:12:37.464
<i>Maybe? Maybe?</i>

150
00:12:37.631 --> 00:12:40.133
<i>Okay. Let's get out of here, okay?</i>

151
00:12:55.107 --> 00:12:57.525
That place ain't changed
much from last year.

152
00:12:57.693 --> 00:12:59.486
Are we done?

153
00:12:59.779 --> 00:13:01.988
Hey, how you
doing, Mick?

154
00:13:04.867 --> 00:13:06.826
That sign is falling apart,
Paulie.

155
00:13:06.994 --> 00:13:10.330
The whole world is
falling apart. Look at us.

156
00:13:10.498 --> 00:13:12.874
Don't talk crazy, Paulie.

157
00:13:13.083 --> 00:13:18.379
You know, I think if you live
someplace long enough,
you are that place.

158
00:13:18.964 --> 00:13:21.549
I ain't no
talking building.

159
00:13:21.717 --> 00:13:23.968
Come on,
it's getting late, Rocko.

160
00:13:24.261 --> 00:13:27.013
I get a headache from this train.

161
00:13:46.909 --> 00:13:49.786
I remember when
she was standing there,

162
00:13:49.954 --> 00:13:53.665
all nervous and shy,
with this little smile.

163
00:13:54.291 --> 00:13:57.502
And all I wanted her to do
was trust me.

164
00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:02.799
She did.

165
00:14:03.884 --> 00:14:06.302
She did.
You done?

166
00:14:21.861 --> 00:14:23.361
PAULIE:
How long are we staying here?

167
00:14:23.529 --> 00:14:24.654
ROCKY:
Not long.

168
00:14:24.822 --> 00:14:27.198
PAULIE:
Well, I'm glad they tore
this ice rink down.

169
00:14:27.366 --> 00:14:28.616
Come on.

170
00:14:28.784 --> 00:14:32.579
You heard me.
I'm happy they tore it apart.

171
00:14:36.208 --> 00:14:40.670
First time I walked your sister
across this ice, we was over there.

172
00:14:40.838 --> 00:14:44.340
She was nervous, but I wasn't
so great on the blades either.

173
00:14:44.508 --> 00:14:48.553
Ice is stupid. People standing
on ice are more stupid.

174
00:14:49.805 --> 00:14:53.766
And over there,
when she was falling,

175
00:14:54.101 --> 00:14:55.560
and my hand grabbed her,

176
00:14:56.687 --> 00:15:00.565
and I got her arm through that coat,
I could feel it.

177
00:15:01.358 --> 00:15:03.151
Electric.

178
00:15:03.652 --> 00:15:06.070
You said the same thing
last year, Rock.

179
00:15:07.364 --> 00:15:08.656
Did I?

180
00:15:08.824 --> 00:15:10.992
ADRIAN:
--so you better develop your brain.

181
00:15:11.160 --> 00:15:13.036
You're left-handed.
ROCKY: Absolutely.

182
00:15:13.203 --> 00:15:15.496
PAULIE:
Come on, Rock. Let's go.

183
00:15:17.958 --> 00:15:21.753
We're done. There's no place
to sit down around here.

184
00:15:21.921 --> 00:15:23.212
Ah, it's all right.

185
00:15:23.380 --> 00:15:27.717
It ain't all right! It's depressing
and freaking cold!

186
00:15:28.469 --> 00:15:30.094
What's the matter
with you, Paulie?

187
00:15:30.471 --> 00:15:32.555
You're living backwards,
Rocko!

188
00:15:32.723 --> 00:15:36.225
Change the channel from yesterday!
Yesterday wasn't so great!

189
00:15:36.393 --> 00:15:38.811
It was to me.
Not to me!

190
00:15:40.689 --> 00:15:43.858
You treated her good.
You had the good times.

191
00:15:44.735 --> 00:15:48.279
I treated her bad.
I don't have to think about this.

192
00:15:49.698 --> 00:15:51.866
She always loved you, Paulie.

193
00:15:56.163 --> 00:15:59.415
Sorry, Rocko,
I can't do this no more.

194
00:16:53.220 --> 00:16:55.221
[COMMENTATOR SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY ON TV]

195
00:16:55.389 --> 00:16:57.557
[CROWD CHEERING ON TV]

196
00:17:00.561 --> 00:17:02.395
[ALL CHATTERING]

197
00:17:12.281 --> 00:17:13.448
Can I help you?

198
00:17:13.824 --> 00:17:16.492
No, no, I used to come down
to this place a long time ago.

199
00:17:16.660 --> 00:17:19.287
I was just looking around.
No big deal.

200
00:17:20.164 --> 00:17:21.414
Can I get you a drink?

201
00:17:23.333 --> 00:17:26.669
All right. Maybe just a short beer.
Okay.

202
00:17:35.596 --> 00:17:37.388
MAN:
Go. Go on.

203
00:17:38.348 --> 00:17:40.183
Yeah, go on.
Get him to buy a round.

204
00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:42.268
Get him to buy a round.
Go.

205
00:17:42.644 --> 00:17:45.480
Get him to-- He's got it.
He's spending money.

206
00:17:45.647 --> 00:17:50.860
Listen, I don't mean to
cross the line or anything,

207
00:17:51.028 --> 00:17:54.030
but I read about your wife's
passing a few years back.

208
00:17:54.198 --> 00:17:55.782
Yeah, it was woman cancer.

209
00:17:55.949 --> 00:17:58.910
Yeah. I always heard
she was a nice person.

210
00:17:59.078 --> 00:18:01.496
Yeah, the best.

211
00:18:02.539 --> 00:18:04.916
Do I know you?
We met a long time ago.

212
00:18:05.417 --> 00:18:06.501
We did?

213
00:18:06.668 --> 00:18:09.170
When I was a kid,
you walked me home.

214
00:18:09.338 --> 00:18:12.632
I did?
Told me to stop smoking and things.

215
00:18:14.176 --> 00:18:16.344
Stop smoking...

216
00:18:17.012 --> 00:18:20.556
Are you Little Marie
that used to hang out at
that Atomic Hoagie shop?

217
00:18:20.724 --> 00:18:22.558
Yeah, that's right.

218
00:18:23.185 --> 00:18:25.561
Yeah, now I remember.
I walked you home.

219
00:18:25.729 --> 00:18:29.607
When you got there,
you turned around and said,
"Screw you, creepo."

220
00:18:29.775 --> 00:18:32.110
I didn't say that.
Yeah, you did.

221
00:18:32.277 --> 00:18:35.696
You sure?
Great insults last a long time.

222
00:18:35.864 --> 00:18:39.242
Yo! Yo, is that you?
Is that really you?

223
00:18:39.785 --> 00:18:42.120
How you doing?
I think he wants to drink alone.

224
00:18:42.371 --> 00:18:45.331
Well, then give him his drink,
then. I ain't stopping you.

225
00:18:45.541 --> 00:18:48.960
What's that, your man
or something? No, I don't think so.

226
00:18:51.797 --> 00:18:55.133
Anyway, me and my friends,
we're right down there.

227
00:18:55.300 --> 00:18:58.594
You think you could buy us
a round? Come on, you got
the money. Just one round.

228
00:18:58.762 --> 00:19:01.681
Hey. Thank you.

229
