01:14:11.655 --> 01:14:14.574
Hello, I'm Jim Lampley with
Larry Merchant and Max Kellerman,

1143
01:14:14.741 --> 01:14:17.952
live from the Mandalay Bay Hotel
in Las Vegas, where we anticipate

1144
01:14:18.120 --> 01:14:21.330
one of the most outrageous and
compelling events in boxing history.

1145
01:14:21.498 --> 01:14:25.209
The unappreciated heavyweight
champion, Mason "The Line" Dixon,

1146
01:14:25.377 --> 01:14:27.253
<i>putting his reputation
on the line</i>

1147
01:14:27.421 --> 01:14:31.382
<i>against legendary
ex-ex-ex-champion, Rocky Balboa.</i>

1148
01:14:31.550 --> 01:14:34.719
<i>Even though most see this as more
of a glorified sparring session,</i>

1149
01:14:34.887 --> 01:14:36.846
the energy in the room is electric.

1150
01:14:37.014 --> 01:14:39.098
Larry, why is this billed
as an exhibition?

1151
01:14:39.266 --> 01:14:43.436
Wild guess: So they wouldn't
have to call it an execution.

1152
01:14:44.229 --> 01:14:49.442
Zacariah 4:6 says,
"It is not by strength, not by might,

1153
01:14:49.610 --> 01:14:53.404
but by his spirit we have
already claimed the victory

1154
01:14:53.572 --> 01:14:56.240
in our Lord Jesus Christ."

1155
01:14:56.909 --> 01:14:58.576
Good luck, Rocky.

1156
01:14:58.744 --> 01:15:01.037
Thanks, Spider.
Appreciate it.

1157
01:15:01.246 --> 01:15:03.664
[CROWD CHEERING NEARBY]

1158
01:15:12.132 --> 01:15:15.426
Nobody's expecting much, I think,
from the way-past-his-prime

1159
01:15:15.594 --> 01:15:17.678
former champ,
Rocky Balboa.

1160
01:15:18.138 --> 01:15:21.432
Rock, I gotta talk to you.

1161
01:15:22.184 --> 01:15:28.022
Look, I know you got a lot of stuff
you gotta get out of your system.

1162
01:15:28.941 --> 01:15:33.486
Tonight you do it. Right?
Get rid of the damn beast,

1163
01:15:33.654 --> 01:15:38.491
let it be done, once and for all.
Please, I love you.

1164
01:15:39.409 --> 01:15:43.037
CROWD [CHANTING]:
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1165
01:15:47.834 --> 01:15:52.255
There go the lights.
The buzz is building
toward a roaring crescendo.

1166
01:16:00.973 --> 01:16:03.975
[FRANK SINATRA'S "HIGH HOPES"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

1167
01:16:08.146 --> 01:16:11.357
Where did that come from?
I told you.

1168
01:16:11.525 --> 01:16:13.526
I love Sinatra.

1169
01:16:14.194 --> 01:16:16.237
He's very good, Sinatra.

1170
01:16:16.405 --> 01:16:19.448
MAN: Let's go.
Very good.

1171
01:16:21.660 --> 01:16:26.163
MERCHANT:
And here comes Rocky Balboa,
veteran of the wars,

1172
01:16:26.373 --> 01:16:29.041
here for one more last hurrah.

1173
01:16:29.209 --> 01:16:32.169
LAMPLEY:
Or the Last Supper, perhaps,
with him as the main course.

1174
01:16:32.337 --> 01:16:34.964
What's that music?
You can't be serious.

1175
01:16:35.132 --> 01:16:37.842
MERCHANT: "High Hopes"?
Talk about wishful thinking.

1176
01:16:38.051 --> 01:16:41.512
Well, maybe no hopes is more
realistic. Anyway, the crowd likes it.

1177
01:16:42.347 --> 01:16:45.558
KELLERMAN:
Look at the Italian Stallion.
Cool and relaxed.

1178
01:16:45.726 --> 01:16:49.478
LAMPLEY:
Rocky's an off-the-board underdog,
and they don't care at all.

1179
01:16:49.646 --> 01:16:53.399
KELLERMAN:
This is about his pride and dignity
and his punch, guys.

1180
01:16:53.650 --> 01:16:56.193
The last thing to go
is a guy's punch.

1181
01:16:56.361 --> 01:16:59.822
Rocky always has
that puncher's chance.

1182
01:17:00.574 --> 01:17:02.700
[CROWD CHEERING]

1183
01:17:04.161 --> 01:17:08.247
LAMPLEY:
Rocky Balboa is still, as you
can hear, the people's champion.

1184
01:17:08.415 --> 01:17:10.875
KELLERMAN:
Prediction, guys:
For at least two rounds,

1185
01:17:11.043 --> 01:17:12.752
Dixon's gonna have
his hands full.

1186
01:17:12.919 --> 01:17:16.964
MERCHANT:
Two whole rounds? We have
a cockeyed optimist in the house.

1187
01:17:17.924 --> 01:17:19.759
How you doing?
LAMPLEY: The crowd wants to see

1188
01:17:19.926 --> 01:17:21.594
something real,
or at least--

1189
01:17:21.762 --> 01:17:23.804
Rocky Balboa just
asked me how I'm doing.

1190
01:17:23.972 --> 01:17:28.643
I grew up watching this guy.
I never thought I'd be calling
one of his fights.

1191
01:17:29.144 --> 01:17:31.854
This is unbelievable.
I'm a fan, I can't help it.

1192
01:17:32.022 --> 01:17:33.689
LAMPLEY:
Now here comes Mason Dixon.

1193
01:17:33.857 --> 01:17:36.859
[THREE 6 MAFIA'S "IT'S A FIGHT"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

1194
01:17:37.027 --> 01:17:39.111
[CROWD BOOING]

1195
01:17:43.533 --> 01:17:45.534
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

1196
01:18:08.892 --> 01:18:11.352
LAMPLEY:
Mason Dixon establishing
his presence in the ring.

1197
01:18:11.520 --> 01:18:15.272
And suddenly now a conversation
breaking out at ringside.

1198
01:18:15.440 --> 01:18:18.192
Mike Tyson calling out
Mason "The Line" Dixon.

1199
01:18:18.360 --> 01:18:20.903
You can't call no shots here.
I'm the champ.

1200
01:18:21.071 --> 01:18:23.447
You not doing nothing.
This is charity work.

1201
01:18:23.615 --> 01:18:26.659
You got that midget
with you right there.

1202
01:18:30.122 --> 01:18:31.205
[BELL RINGS]

1203
01:18:31.373 --> 01:18:35.251
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to the Mandalay Bay

1204
01:18:35.419 --> 01:18:39.004
resort and casino of Las Vegas.

1205
01:18:39.172 --> 01:18:42.633
And a special main event
of the evening,

1206
01:18:42.801 --> 01:18:46.137
10 rounds of
heavyweight excitement,

1207
01:18:46.304 --> 01:18:48.723
sanctioned by the Nevada
State Athletic Commission.

1208
01:18:48.890 --> 01:18:54.353
And when the bell rings, the referee
in charge of the action, Joe Cortez.

1209
01:18:54.521 --> 01:18:57.648
And now, for the thousands
in attendance

1210
01:18:57.816 --> 01:19:03.571
and the millions watching around
the world, ladies and gentlemen,

1211
01:19:03.739 --> 01:19:08.576
let's get ready to rumble!

1212
01:19:08.744 --> 01:19:10.745
[CROWD CHEERING]

1213
01:19:11.705 --> 01:19:14.874
Introducing first,
fighting out of the blue corner,

1214
01:19:15.041 --> 01:19:19.754
wearing black with gold,
official weight, 217 pounds.

1215
01:19:19.921 --> 01:19:25.259
His professional record,
57 victories, including 54 knockouts,
with 23 defeats and one draw.

1216
01:19:25.427 --> 01:19:27.762
CROWD [CHANTING]:
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1217
01:19:27.929 --> 01:19:31.098
BUFFER:
He is the fighting pride
of Philadelphia,

1218
01:19:31.349 --> 01:19:35.728
the two-time heavyweight
champion of the world,

1219
01:19:35.896 --> 01:19:38.022
"The Italian Stallion,"

1220
01:19:38.190 --> 01:19:42.777
Rocky...

1221
01:19:42.944 --> 01:19:45.321
Balboa!

1222
01:19:45.530 --> 01:19:47.531
[ALL CHEERING]

1223
01:19:48.366 --> 01:19:49.950
Hope he gets his head busted.

1224
01:19:51.995 --> 01:19:53.913
Shut up.

1225
01:19:56.708 --> 01:19:59.502
BUFFER: Across the ring,
fighting out of the red corner,

1226
01:19:59.669 --> 01:20:03.464
wearing white with blue,
official weight, 221 pounds.

1227
01:20:03.715 --> 01:20:08.719
He has a perfect professional record,
consisting of 33 bouts,

1228
01:20:08.887 --> 01:20:12.139
33 victories,
including 30 knockouts.

1229
01:20:12.307 --> 01:20:14.266
Originally from Tampa, Florida,

1230
01:20:14.434 --> 01:20:17.478
but now fighting out
of Las Vegas, Nevada,

1231
01:20:17.646 --> 01:20:21.982
the reigning undisputed,
undefeated

1232
01:20:22.150 --> 01:20:25.110
heavyweight champion
of the world,

1233
01:20:25.278 --> 01:20:28.781
Mason "The Line"...

1234
01:20:28.949 --> 01:20:31.200
Dixon!

1235
01:20:31.368 --> 01:20:33.536
[CROWD BOOING]

1236
01:20:37.082 --> 01:20:38.749
CORTEZ:
All right, gentlemen.

1237
01:20:38.917 --> 01:20:42.253
All right, Mason, Rocky. We went
over the rules in the dressing room.

1238
01:20:42.420 --> 01:20:46.465
I expect a good, clean fight. Watch
the kidney punches, rabbit punches,

1239
01:20:46.633 --> 01:20:49.844
those low blows, be careful
with those. Give me good
sportsmanlike conduct.

1240
01:20:50.011 --> 01:20:53.722
Remember, gentlemen, I'm fair
but I'm firm. Touch them up!

1241
01:20:53.890 --> 01:20:55.140
Enjoy the ride.

1242
01:20:55.308 --> 01:20:57.560
LAMPLEY:
The champ is not in the best
shape we've seen him in.

1243
01:20:57.727 --> 01:20:59.937
Maybe he plans to phone this in
and go home early.

1244
01:21:00.105 --> 01:21:02.523
That wouldn't be a surprise.
Glad you could make it.

1245
01:21:02.691 --> 01:21:05.317
KELLERMAN:
One thing about Rocky
we know for sure:

1246
01:21:05.485 --> 01:21:07.736
This guy's showing up in shape.

1247
01:21:07.904 --> 01:21:10.739
The old man's crazy.
He's gotta be crazy. He's in here.

1248
01:21:10.907 --> 01:21:12.825
Okay.
Take it easy. This is an exhibition.

1249
01:21:12.993 --> 01:21:14.451
All right? Do it to him.

1250
01:21:14.619 --> 01:21:17.830
You got three rounds to set a pace.
Every time you hit him, make a dent.

1251
01:21:17.998 --> 01:21:19.957
Got it.
KELLERMAN: The moments before

1252
01:21:20.125 --> 01:21:23.627
a Rocky Balboa fight?
I can't believe it's here!

1253
01:21:23.837 --> 01:21:24.837
[BELL RINGS]

1254
01:21:25.005 --> 01:21:26.005
LAMPLEY:
Round one begins.

1255
01:21:26.172 --> 01:21:29.884
KELLERMAN:
If old George Foreman shocked
the world with one punch,

1256
01:21:30.051 --> 01:21:32.177
why can't old Rocky Balboa?

1257
01:21:32.345 --> 01:21:34.680
LAMPLEY:
And as much excitement
as there is in the arena,

1258
01:21:34.848 --> 01:21:37.224
there's a sense of
foreboding as well.

1259
01:21:41.563 --> 01:21:45.232
And now, Mason "The Line" Dixon
goes to work with his jab as though

1260
01:21:45.400 --> 01:21:49.278
he's fighting against the
number one challenger in
the heavyweight division.

1261
01:21:49.696 --> 01:21:51.614
KELLERMAN:
See, this is to be expected early on.

1262
01:21:51.781 --> 01:21:54.491
You knew the champ would
control the distance with his jab,

1263
01:21:54.659 --> 01:21:56.660
his height, his range.

1264
01:21:58.038 --> 01:22:01.165
LAMPLEY:
Balboa looking to get in a shot,
misses wildly.

1265
01:22:01.333 --> 01:22:03.167
Did you like that?

1266
01:22:03.627 --> 01:22:06.754
MERCHANT:
It looks like a speed bag
against a punching bag.

1267
01:22:06.963 --> 01:22:08.547
LAMPLEY:
Rocky's understandably frustrated,

1268
01:22:08.715 --> 01:22:11.050
but he came out of retirement
to get into a fight.

1269
01:22:11.217 --> 01:22:13.802
KELLERMAN:
Guys named Rocky
don't like to be toyed with.

1270
01:22:13.970 --> 01:22:15.679
One punch could still
turn it around.

1271
01:22:15.847 --> 01:22:18.974
MERCHANT: Apparently he forgot
his arthritis meds this morning.

1272
01:22:19.267 --> 01:22:20.726
LAMPLEY:
Rocky misses.

1273
01:22:21.102 --> 01:22:24.855
There's a meat-seeking missile on
the point of the chin by the champ.

1274
01:22:25.023 --> 01:22:26.607
More pinpoint jabs by Dixon.

1275
01:22:26.775 --> 01:22:27.942
CROWD [CHANTING]:
Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!

1276
01:22:28.109 --> 01:22:31.236
LAMPLEY:
And there's a hard right hand
and a left and a right by Balboa!

1277
01:22:31.404 --> 01:22:34.365
He drives Dixon into the ropes
with a series of shots!

1278
01:22:34.532 --> 01:22:35.991
And the crowd goes berserk!

1279
01:22:36.159 --> 01:22:37.910
[CROWD CHEERING]

1280
01:22:41.831 --> 01:22:46.085
Dixon punishing Balboa for the
temerity of landing those shots.

1281
01:22:46.294 --> 01:22:47.962
[CROWD BOOING]

1282
01:22:49.589 --> 01:22:54.218
It's toe to toe in the corner.
Balboa and Dixon letting it all go.

1283
01:22:54.386 --> 01:22:56.053
[CROWD CHEERING]

1284
01:22:59.391 --> 01:23:00.766
[BELL RINGS]

1285
01:23:00.934 --> 01:23:03.811
Balboa landing potent combinations
to the head of the champion.

1286
01:23:04.145 --> 01:23:05.396
A wake-up call for Dixon.

1287
01:23:05.563 --> 01:23:07.189
DUKE: You all right?
Yeah, I'm all right.

1288
01:23:07.357 --> 01:23:10.567
The man's got bricks in his gloves.
Where's the stuff in the basement?

1289
01:23:10.735 --> 01:23:12.903
It's still there. It's still there.
He came to battle, okay?

1290
01:23:13.071 --> 01:23:14.571
Trying to knock me out.
Listen.

1291
01:23:14.739 --> 01:23:17.157
If there's a bone he can break,
he's gonna do it.

1292
01:23:17.325 --> 01:23:19.618
Give the man respect.
What about my respect?

1293
01:23:19.786 --> 01:23:22.621
LAMPLEY:
CompuBox numbers
tell the grisly story here.

1294
01:23:22.789 --> 01:23:25.874
Balboa landed nine of 1 3
punches in that round.

1295
01:23:26.042 --> 01:23:31.213
Dixon landed an incredible
59 out of 69.

1296
01:23:31.381 --> 01:23:32.423
Why don't you listen to me?

1297
01:23:32.590 --> 01:23:34.842
KELLERMAN:
Rocky's been here a million times.

1298
01:23:35.010 --> 01:23:38.220
Coming out to start a round after he
took a beating in the previous one.

1299
01:23:38.388 --> 01:23:41.557
Remember what I said, okay?
I warned him. I warned him.

1300
01:23:42.600 --> 01:23:47.563
LAMPLEY:
He's tired. His legs are
going fast, or already gone.

1301
01:23:47.731 --> 01:23:52.276
KELLERMAN:
And what's truly extraordinary
is that Rocky can still take it.

1302
01:23:52.444 --> 01:23:57.406
MERCHANT:
The boxing commission, which
was criticized for licensing him,

1303
01:23:57.574 --> 01:24:01.785
would be massacred
if something happened to Rocky.

1304
01:24:02.328 --> 01:24:03.328
[GRUNTS]

1305
01:24:05.123 --> 01:24:07.791
LAMPLEY:
And a monstrous straight left hand!
Down goes Rocky!

1306
01:24:07.959 --> 01:24:10.294
And that could conceivably
be the end of the fight!

1307
01:24:10.462 --> 01:24:14.298
That could be the exhibition
right there. But no. Balboa up.

1308
01:24:14.466 --> 01:24:18.761
Referee Joe Cortez asks if he wants
to continue, and Rocky says yes.

1309
01:24:18.928 --> 01:24:21.805
KELLERMAN:
Even Rocky Balboa could be
too brave for his own good.

1310
01:24:21.973 --> 01:24:25.559
LAMPLEY:
Dixon comes right back to try to
finish it. Balboa almost went down!

1311
01:24:25.727 --> 01:24:27.728
MERCHANT:
Rocky actually shoves Dixon back.

1312
01:24:27.896 --> 01:24:30.439
LAMPLEY:
As Dixon lands these brutal shots.

1313
01:24:30.607 --> 01:24:31.815
Cover up! Cover up!

1314
01:24:31.983 --> 01:24:33.150
LAMPLEY:
Open shots at close range.

1315
01:24:33.318 --> 01:24:35.861
Right and left hands,
and down goes Balboa!

1316
01:24:36.029 --> 01:24:39.406
Perhaps for the last time
in his fighting career!

1317
01:24:39.574 --> 01:24:41.992
MERCHANT: That should do it.
CORTEZ: Three! Four!

1318
01:24:42.160 --> 01:24:44.495
Five! Six!

1319
01:24:44.662 --> 01:24:46.288
Get up! Get up!
CORTEZ: Seven!

1320
01:24:46.456 --> 01:24:48.248
Eight! Nine!

1321
01:24:49.667 --> 01:24:50.959
How do you feel, man?
You okay?

1322
01:24:51.127 --> 01:24:52.878
LAMPLEY:
Now Rocky is furious with himself.

1323
01:24:53.046 --> 01:24:55.672
He convinces Cortez
he wants to keep fighting.

1324
01:24:55.840 --> 01:24:57.674
KELLERMAN:
Dixon's pointing at the ref to end it.

1325
01:24:57.842 --> 01:24:59.968
Rocky waving his arms
and saying he's fine.

1326
01:25:00.136 --> 01:25:02.304
He wants to go on!
Let it go! Let it go!

1327
01:25:03.223 --> 01:25:06.308
LAMPLEY:
And Balboa comes back!
With a left and a right

1328
01:25:06.476 --> 01:25:10.354
and bulls Dixon into the ropes
for the second round in a row!

1329
01:25:11.564 --> 01:25:12.940
Back comes Dixon
with brutal left-hand shots.

1330
01:25:13.108 --> 01:25:14.149
[♪♪♪]

1331
01:25:14.317 --> 01:25:16.527
Dixon hurt his hand there!
Go after him!

1332
01:25:16.694 --> 01:25:18.362
KELLERMAN:
This is Rocky's best chance!

1333
01:25:18.530 --> 01:25:20.739
The champ obviously hurt
his hand on Rocky's hip!

1334
01:25:20.907 --> 01:25:24.743
LAMPLEY:
And Balboa immediately going to
work to the body! Huge right hook!

1335
01:25:24.911 --> 01:25:28.497
Balboa ripping away at Dixon's body!
These are big punches.

1336
01:25:28.706 --> 01:25:32.459
CROWD [CHANTING]:
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1337
01:25:33.878 --> 01:25:34.920
Yes!

1338
01:25:35.130 --> 01:25:37.214
[ALL CHEERING]

1339
01:25:37.382 --> 01:25:41.844
LAMPLEY: Rocky Balboa
has knocked the reigning
heavyweight champion down!

1340
01:25:42.011 --> 01:25:43.887
You hurt him!
LAMPLEY: Mason "The Line" Dixon

1341
01:25:44.055 --> 01:25:46.140
has never taken
this kind of punishment

1342
01:25:46.307 --> 01:25:48.475
in his entire professional career!

1343
01:25:48.643 --> 01:25:52.646
KELLERMAN: Maybe
he's clearing his head, but the
body shots really caved in his ribs.

1344
01:25:52.814 --> 01:25:55.482
LAMPLEY:
Balboa is thinking knockout himself!

1345
01:25:55.650 --> 01:25:59.194
KELLERMAN:
Another counterhook by Balboa,
followed by two more!

1346
01:25:59.362 --> 01:26:01.864
LAMPLEY:
Dixon fires back his own hooks!
Now Rocky's stunned.

1347
01:26:02.031 --> 01:26:04.575
It's an all-out war along the ropes

1348
01:26:04.742 --> 01:26:07.619
as round two comes to a close
amid a giant tumult in the ring!

1349
01:26:07.787 --> 01:26:09.288
[BELL RINGS]

1350
01:26:10.456 --> 01:26:12.082
KELLERMAN:
Incredible.

1351
01:26:12.250 --> 01:26:13.917
All right!

1352
01:26:14.085 --> 01:26:15.878
Welcome to Rockyland.

1353
01:26:16.045 --> 01:26:17.880
[♪♪♪]

1354
01:26:19.966 --> 01:26:22.426
How's the hand?
My hand's broken.

1355
01:26:24.512 --> 01:26:26.555
We lose, it's your ass! Your ass!

1356
01:26:26.723 --> 01:26:29.016
It will numb up on you
in a few rounds.

1357
01:26:29.184 --> 01:26:32.769
Once that hand numbs up,
Dixon will be able to throw it hard.

1358
01:26:32.937 --> 01:26:35.355
Until then, here is Rocky's chance.

1359
01:26:35.523 --> 01:26:38.275
No reverse!
Take the pain, champ.

1360
01:26:38.443 --> 01:26:41.236
Stay on him! Everybody thought
this was a joke, including me!

1361
01:26:41.404 --> 01:26:44.031
Now nobody's laughing!
Stay on him! You go get him!

1362
01:26:44.782 --> 01:26:46.700
Go out strong!

1363
01:26:58.504 --> 01:26:59.504
Keep him off you!

1364
01:27:00.173 --> 01:27:01.465
[GRUNTING]

1365
01:27:03.384 --> 01:27:04.384
That's it! That's it!

1366
01:27:06.387 --> 01:27:07.721
[BELL RINGING]

1367
01:27:07.931 --> 01:27:08.931
Yeah!

1368
01:27:18.816 --> 01:27:20.901
DUKE: You won that round.
Break him down.

1369
01:27:26.574 --> 01:27:28.575
Bomb him! Bomb him!

1370
01:27:34.290 --> 01:27:35.499
Yeah!

1371
01:27:39.420 --> 01:27:41.713
Just keep throwing
them bombs!

1372
01:27:48.137 --> 01:27:50.097
[GROANS]

1373
01:27:53.518 --> 01:27:54.685
Come on.

1374
01:27:56.187 --> 01:27:58.188
[♪♪♪]

1375
01:28:02.193 --> 01:28:04.278
You can do this.

1376
01:28:05.154 --> 01:28:07.906
Rocko. Rocko.

1377
01:28:14.205 --> 01:28:15.706
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1378
01:28:16.541 --> 01:28:18.875
Yeah, come on, go!

1379
01:28:19.127 --> 01:28:21.211
[♪♪♪]

1380
01:28:46.571 --> 01:28:48.322
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

1381
01:29:15.933 --> 01:29:17.809
Go through him!
Run over him!

1382
01:29:17.977 --> 01:29:19.186
[BELL RINGS]

1383
01:29:33.284 --> 01:29:34.493
Unload on him!

1384
01:29:36.371 --> 01:29:37.371
Get down, Mason!

1385
01:29:46.672 --> 01:29:48.048
[BELL RINGS]

1386
01:29:49.175 --> 01:29:51.176
KELLERMAN:
They're leaving nothing
on the table, guys.

1387
01:29:51.386 --> 01:29:55.889
MERCHANT:
The fans are still standing. They may
not be able to sit down for a week.

1388
01:29:56.057 --> 01:29:58.809
You're doing great!
I'm doing better than I thought.

1389
01:29:58.976 --> 01:30:02.813
CORTEZ: You sure he's okay?
I've had worse.

1390
01:30:02.980 --> 01:30:06.691
Toe to toe, one round to go. Who
would've believed this was possible?

1391
01:30:06.859 --> 01:30:09.236
Can you see out of that eye?
Let me talk to him.

1392
01:30:09.654 --> 01:30:11.655
Don't take any more chances
than you have to.

1393
01:30:11.823 --> 01:30:14.825
There's nothing more to prove, Pop.
There's nothing more to prove.

1394
01:30:14.992 --> 01:30:17.119
I gotta go out the way
I gotta go out.

1395
01:30:17.286 --> 01:30:18.829
PAULIE:
You can do it, Rocko!

1396
01:30:19.038 --> 01:30:21.331
One more round, we go home.
Okay, then do it.

1397
01:30:21.499 --> 01:30:25.043
MERCHANT:
There's an old saying that
every great champion has

1398
01:30:25.211 --> 01:30:28.422
one great fight left in him,
and Rocky is proving it so far.

1399
01:30:28.589 --> 01:30:30.006
[BELL RINGS]

1400
01:30:30.675 --> 01:30:33.885
CORTEZ: Come on. Touch them up.
Rocko! The last round of your life!

1401
01:30:34.053 --> 01:30:35.720
CORTEZ: Come on, guys.
The last round!

1402
01:30:35.888 --> 01:30:38.265
Come on. Touch them up,
let's go. Touch them up.

1403
01:30:38.933 --> 01:30:41.852
You are one crazy old man.
You'll get there.

1404
01:30:42.311 --> 01:30:43.478
CORTEZ:
Let's go.

1405
01:30:43.771 --> 01:30:47.023
LAMPLEY:
Tenth round of a scheduled 1 0.
Who would ever have dreamed

1406
01:30:47.191 --> 01:30:51.987
that Rocky Balboa would still be
in this quote, "exhibition," against

1407
01:30:52.155 --> 01:30:54.906
the heavyweight champion?
You can do it! Come on!

1408
01:30:55.074 --> 01:30:59.411
KELLERMAN:
This fight is as though Dixon
got on-the-job training in courage.

1409
01:31:00.538 --> 01:31:01.830
Cover up! Cover up!

1410
01:31:01.998 --> 01:31:03.290
KELLERMAN:
They're both in a pain-free zone!

1411
01:31:03.458 --> 01:31:06.710
These guys are fighting
in another dimension right now!

1412
01:31:06.878 --> 01:31:10.922
LAMPLEY:
Beyond belief! Balboa just walking
straight into Dixon's punches.

1413
01:31:11.090 --> 01:31:13.717
Target practice for Dixon.

1414
01:31:17.138 --> 01:31:19.598
KELLERMAN:
They're exchanging right hooks!
Balboa's drilled!

1415
01:31:19.765 --> 01:31:23.018
Here comes Dixon! He's exhausted
from just punching the man!

1416
01:31:24.896 --> 01:31:26.229
Knock this bum out, Mase!

1417
01:31:28.733 --> 01:31:29.858
[CROWD GROANS]

1418
01:31:30.026 --> 01:31:31.860
[♪♪♪]

1419
01:31:38.743 --> 01:31:42.787
ROCKY:
<i>What is it you said to the kid?
It ain't about how hard you hit.</i>

1420
01:31:42.955 --> 01:31:47.000
<i>It's about how hard you can get hit
and keep moving forward.</i>

1421
01:31:47.293 --> 01:31:51.004
<i>How much you can take
and keep moving forward.</i>

1422
01:31:51.172 --> 01:31:52.964
CROWD: <i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>
ROCKY: <i>Get up.</i>

1423
01:31:53.132 --> 01:31:55.133
Let's go! Get up!
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1424
01:31:55.343 --> 01:31:58.053
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1425
01:31:58.262 --> 01:32:00.180
ROCKY:
<i>Get up.</i>

1426
01:32:00.348 --> 01:32:03.350
[♪♪♪]

1427
01:32:21.244 --> 01:32:24.829
LAMPLEY:
Another monster body shot. Rocky's
ancestors must have felt that one.

1428
01:32:24.997 --> 01:32:27.082
Come on, Rocky!
Start moving those hands!

1429
01:32:27.291 --> 01:32:29.000
LAMPLEY:
Less than two minutes to go.

1430
01:32:29.168 --> 01:32:31.545
The crowd is astonished
that Balboa got up.

1431
01:32:31.712 --> 01:32:34.214
Come on!
Turn it over! All the way through!

1432
01:32:34.632 --> 01:32:36.341
LAMPLEY:
And retaliates with fury!

1433
01:32:39.887 --> 01:32:41.096
Chop him down!

1434
01:32:44.767 --> 01:32:46.434
Come on, Rocky! Come on!

1435
01:32:48.854 --> 01:32:50.438
Take him out now!

1436
01:32:51.566 --> 01:32:53.650
LAMPLEY:
They're trading shots again!

1437
01:32:53.818 --> 01:32:57.404
KELLERMAN:
Balboa is trying to hit
anything and anywhere!

1438
01:32:59.740 --> 01:33:01.074
Win it! Win it!

1439
01:33:09.000 --> 01:33:10.041
[BELL RINGING]

1440
01:33:10.209 --> 01:33:11.710
Yes!

1441
01:33:12.253 --> 01:33:14.254
[♪♪♪]

1442
01:33:20.511 --> 01:33:23.346
You're a great champion.
You got heart.

1443
01:33:23.514 --> 01:33:25.265
Thanks for the opportunity.
Good man.

1444
01:33:28.311 --> 01:33:31.396
That was unbelievable. That was
the greatest thing I've ever seen.

1445
01:33:33.524 --> 01:33:36.276
You did it. That's the kind
of fighting you're talking about.

1446
01:33:37.862 --> 01:33:39.821
ROCKY:
Hey, Paulie.

1447
01:33:40.031 --> 01:33:42.866
That beast is gone now.
The beast is out.

1448
01:33:43.034 --> 01:33:46.828
One of the most overused words
in sports, guys, is "incredible."

1449
01:33:46.996 --> 01:33:51.291
I hate to say it.
This is incredible.

1450
01:33:52.668 --> 01:33:54.336
Let's go!

1451
01:33:57.048 --> 01:34:00.717
BUFFER:
Ladies and gentlemen,
before we go to the scorecards,

1452
01:34:00.885 --> 01:34:07.015
a round of applause for these
two heavyweight warriors!

1453
01:34:11.646 --> 01:34:15.649
We have a split decision.

1454
01:34:18.277 --> 01:34:23.156
Adelaide Byrd scores it 95-94,

1455
01:34:23.324 --> 01:34:25.116
Dixon.

1456
01:34:26.410 --> 01:34:30.830
Chuck Giampa has it 95-94,

1457
01:34:30.998 --> 01:34:32.957
Balboa.

1458
01:34:33.668 --> 01:34:36.836
CROWD:
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1459
01:34:40.132 --> 01:34:45.011
And Bill Graham scores it 95-94

1460
01:34:45.179 --> 01:34:50.350
for the winner by split decision,
and still undefeated

1461
01:34:50.518 --> 01:34:53.395
the heavyweight champion
of the world,

1462
01:34:53.562 --> 01:34:59.275
Mason "The Line" Dixon!

1463
01:35:01.654 --> 01:35:04.656
CROWD:
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1464
01:35:50.578 --> 01:35:53.037
[♪♪♪]

1465
01:35:56.333 --> 01:35:59.294
You know, I couldn't have
done nothing without you.

1466
01:36:01.756 --> 01:36:04.340
Yo, Adrian, we did it.

1467
01:36:11.098 --> 01:36:12.849
We did it.

1468
01:36:52.389 --> 01:36:55.892
[BILL CONTI'S "GONNA FLY NOW"
PLAYING]

1469
01:39:32.549 --> 01:39:34.717
[♪♪♪]

